The paper discusses the application of deep learning, specifically convolutional neural networks, for image segmentation in connectomics. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel architecture that utilizes skip connections and residual networks, which are popular techniques in deep learning research, indicating a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with electron microscopy data, which is a type of imaging data, suggesting a possible fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
